| ![][image3] | **RUN A SCREAMING FROG CRAWL** Start by [downloading ScreamingFrog](https://www.screamingfrog.co.uk/seo-spider/) from the tool's official website. Once downloaded, login to account with the provided Keeper login details. Begin by entering the client’s website in the search bar and selecting “Start”  You may have to wait a while for the program to run in the background. If it’s a large site, move onto Ahrefs and come back to ScreamingFrog when finished. |
| ![][image4] | **SAVE YOUR INTENRAL\_ALL FILE** Once the program has finished crawling the website, click on a row within the “Address” column and then highlight them all by pressing CMD \+ A (![][image5]) on macbook and CTRL \+A on Windows. Now that all of the website’s assets have been selected, click on the export button. The file name should be internal\_all.csv. Save the file in a place you will easily remember. *Note: Please pay attention to which data table within ScreamingFrog you are selecting Export for. Select the same button that is shown within the GIF image to the left.* |
| **![][image6]** | **CLEAN UP INTERNAL\_ALL DATA** Delete all columns except the following: Address Title 1 Meta Description 1 H1-1 H2-1 H2-2 |
| ![][image7] | **IMPORT YOUR INTENRAL\_ALL FILE FOR RETAINING HISTORICAL SITE DATA** Open up the copied spreadsheet from step 1 Create a new sheet in your file and title it “Site Data” In the navigation bar of Google Sheets, go to file and “import.” |
| ![][image8] | You should get a pop up box. Click on the tab that says “Upload” and select the file you downloaded from ScreamingFrog. Once complete, you should see a new section called “import file.” Make sure you select “Replace current sheet” before importing your data. |
| ![][image9] | **DOWNLOAD THE LATEST CONTENT MAP DATA** Go to the [Google Sheet Template](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17eSmzWETLD8nr0gUhn1sWxtipq6ZIcCyld4-tImNTWE/edit?gid=1877930357#gid=1877930357) and download the template file as a CSV. Save the file in a place you can easily access |
| ![][image10] | **USE AI PROMPT TO ALIGN SITE DATA TO FAMILY LAW CONTENT MAP** Ensure you are logged in to your Rocket Clicks work email and then open [Google Gemini](https://gemini.google.com/) Paste in the [provided prompt](?tab=t.gtns1djha0pk) Click on the \+ sign and select “Upload files” Upload both the ***Family Law Content Map*** as well as the cleaned **internal\_all** file. Wait for the AI to perform its task. It is recommended to leverage this time to pivot to a shorter 15 minute task in your sprint while the AI conducts the audit. Once the AI has completed its report, scroll down until you see the option to ![][image11] Because Google Gemini exports the file without any formatting, move the data into the Google Sheet Template we created in step one  Verify that all URLs accurately relate to what is included in the family law content map.  |
